Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.21,0:00:04.89,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.89,0:00:07.90,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I bring you marvelous illusions that \Nmake this town sparkle at night!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.90,0:00:12.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,For the first time this year, \Nplease enjoy that little guy's miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.69,0:00:23.52,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kaito, class is starting!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.52,0:00:26.50,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Shut up! What do you care?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.54,0:00:26.50,Signs,,0,0,0,,A Notice to Kid the Phantom Thief!\NI possess a Big Jewel.\NBlue Wonder (The Miracle of the Ocean)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.50,0:00:28.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,W-Wha...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.96,0:00:30.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.04,0:00:32.58,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\an6}Preparing
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.01,0:00:35.95,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Young Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.95,0:00:38.43,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't you be in school?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.43,0:00:40.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I left early.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.01,0:00:43.48,Signs,,0,0,0,,A Notice to Kid the Phantom Thief!\NI possess a Big Jewel.\NBlue Wonder (The Miracle of the Ocean)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.42,0:00:43.48,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You must have seen this advertisement.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.86,0:00:46.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But it's a trap, Young Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.94,0:00:49.44,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.44,0:00:50.57,Signs,,0,0,0,,You won't escape from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.57,0:00:52.40,Signs,,0,0,0,,Ultra-high-definition Blu-ray Disc
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.40,0:00:54.28,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Th-This old man...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.28,0:00:57.80,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He's the Suzuki conglomerate's \Nsenior adviser,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.80,0:01:01.24,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,meaning he has unlimited funds\N to prepare for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.24,0:01:04.16,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,On top of that, he's already \Nmade the first move.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.16,0:01:08.29,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,If you're going to steal it, at least \Ndon't send an advance notice this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.29,0:01:10.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You've got it backwards, Jii-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.68,0:01:14.46,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That guy is openly picking a fight with \Nthe unrivaled Kid the Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.46,0:01:17.72,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,So I won't be satisfied unless I slap \Nhim back with an advance notice!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.72,0:01:19.37,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.37,0:01:24.64,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Toichi-sama, too. Once he made up his mind, \Nhe would see it through without fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.64,0:01:27.19,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,no matter how dangerous the circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.19,0:01:29.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'm gonna do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.22,0:01:32.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And I'm counting on you to \Nlay the groundwork, Jii-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.79,0:01:37.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I suppose any further \Narguing would be pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.42,0:01:42.99,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,In that case, Jii will look into all \Nthe details for you, Young Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.49,0:03:16.93,Signs - Thief Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,0)}Kid vs Conan: Miraculous Airwalking
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.77,0:03:16.93,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I put up a good front for Jii-chan,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.93,0:03:20.64,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,but I don't think my usual bag \Nof tricks will work this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.20,0:03:22.65,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Listen to me, Kaito.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.22,0:03:28.61,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Challenging hecklers who interfere with \Nyour magic are always a pain to deal with.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.61,0:03:35.17,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Thinking you'll floor them right away\N is the height of foolishness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.35,0:03:40.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Magic is not a battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.49,0:03:42.75,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's something that entertains many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.75,0:03:44.71,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then what should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.71,0:03:48.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You can divide challenging \Naudience members into two groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.81,0:03:53.33,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The first type wants to stand out \Nmore than the magician.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.33,0:03:56.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,All you can do to deal with that \Nsort of person is silence them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.12,0:03:59.64,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Silence them...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.64,0:04:02.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And then there's the type that is so curious,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.20,0:04:06.11,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,they can't stand not knowing the trick, \Neven if it means interfering with the magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.68,0:04:11.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,For them, don't be bound \Nby theory, but intox...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.82,0:04:14.32,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.82,0:04:16.61,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,{\a6}Don't be bound \Nby theory, but intox...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.61,0:04:19.99,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,{\a6}Don't be bound \Nby theory, but intox...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.38,0:04:19.77,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Right at the important part!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.08,0:04:26.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid will be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.40,0:04:29.78,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But it's on the roof of the museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.78,0:04:33.16,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He can just run up the side of the building!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.16,0:04:35.16,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I bet Kid can do something like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.78,0:04:36.76,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I can picture it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.27,0:04:39.70,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.54,0:04:43.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Has Kid accepted this challenge?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.96,0:04:46.44,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The risk is too high.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.44,0:04:49.44,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I believe he has a 50% chance of success.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.01,0:04:53.23,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Don't be a dumbass! This is exactly \Nthe kind of challenge Kid lives for!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.23,0:04:55.75,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But I wonder how he's gonna steal it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.75,0:04:57.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I can't wait to find out!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.66,0:05:02.87,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Everyone is dying to find out \Nhow I'm going to steal it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.87,0:05:05.28,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Dad was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.28,0:05:08.08,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I can't just win against old man Jirokichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.60,0:05:11.84,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid the Phantom Thief is \Nall about entertaining the audience!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.16,0:05:19.09,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,So this is Blue Wonder...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.09,0:05:22.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I can fly in on a hang glider, \Ngrab it, and go, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.94,0:05:25.23,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.23,0:05:30.51,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Suzuki Jirokichi has hired \Na crackerjack security team.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.51,0:05:33.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That includes a helicopter squad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.69,0:05:35.31,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,There are 20 choppers,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.31,0:05:38.41,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and even now, \Nthey're bringing in more people.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.41,0:05:43.87,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That many choppers flying around will make \Nthe wind currents too choppy for a glider.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.41,0:05:43.87,Signs,,0,0,0,,Suzuki Jirokichi
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.87,0:05:46.19,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Guess I'll think of another \Nmeans of transport.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.19,0:05:48.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I think that will be difficult, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.66,0:05:49.83,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Now what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.24,0:05:53.85,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Information I received from a contractor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.70,0:05:57.04,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Hey, is that even possible?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.04,0:05:59.05,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.62,0:06:05.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Jii-chan, what about the inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.40,0:06:10.21,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,100 surveillance cameras operating \Nat all times, catching everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.21,0:06:12.23,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,There are no blind spots.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.23,0:06:15.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Although cameras mean nothing \Nif I go in disguise!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.66,0:06:22.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A look at the security plan shows \Nthey mean to have {\i1}no one{\i0} inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.20,0:06:24.83,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,So I won't have anyone to impersonate...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.83,0:06:28.17,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,On top of that, the helicopters \Nare equipped with cameras,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.17,0:06:30.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and all of the footage that they capture
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.67,0:06:34.13,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,is sent to this truck parked here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.13,0:06:36.09,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Footage, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.20,0:06:46.97,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Even though it's a special museum \Nexhibition, a helicopter shot?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.97,0:06:51.10,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I don't understand how rich people think.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.30,0:07:02.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Young Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.42,0:07:05.87,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yeah. If he's mixed up in it this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.87,0:07:09.41,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I just have to show him some brilliant magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.41,0:07:12.05,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But how...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.05,0:07:14.03,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I found an opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.03,0:07:17.05,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That just leaves Blue Wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.05,0:07:18.88,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The Miracle of the Sea...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.40,0:07:22.54,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Walking on water is a famous miracle, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.54,0:07:23.64,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.64,0:07:28.60,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then Kid the Phantom Thief \Nwill have to top that miracle!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.60,0:07:30.25,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Th-That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.25,0:07:31.60,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Interesting, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.60,0:07:35.06,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,"Reappearance" is one of the basics of magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.56,0:07:37.98,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This is the same kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.98,0:07:39.39,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.39,0:07:43.18,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Jii-chan, how long will it take you \Nto prepare the tools and set this up?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.18,0:07:45.78,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,If I can have until Saturday...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.78,0:07:47.88,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then it's settled.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.74,0:07:55.42,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\a7}{\fad(0,1000)}I accept your kind invitation. \NThe event will take place this Sunday at 8:00 pm. \NPlease pardon my rudeness for performing\N a preliminary inspection the night before...\NKid the Phantom Thief\N\Np.s. Like the name Blue Wonder, \NI'm going to just walk right over...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.18,0:08:01.78,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,According to Kid's advance notice, he's \Ngoing to do a preliminary inspection tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.78,0:08:04.93,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Will Kid actually appear as promised?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.82,0:08:10.89,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.89,0:08:14.88,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid! Kid! Kid! Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.88,0:08:16.86,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid! Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.86,0:08:19.27,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid! Kid! Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.68,0:08:27.74,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Young Master, we're almost there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.74,0:08:31.29,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then it's time to start the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.97,0:08:38.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you, Jii-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.67,0:08:40.88,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Again, be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.27,0:08:54.98,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,All-righty...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.94,0:09:16.16,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He's floating?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.16,0:09:17.29,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.29,0:09:19.18,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Don't be fooled!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.18,0:09:24.51,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He's just hanging by a wire from \Na black ad balloon or something!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.02,0:09:28.60,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Nab him and get back to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.60,0:09:30.97,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Number 7 helicopter, roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.43,0:09:36.89,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This is helicopter number 7! \NKid isn't hanging from anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.89,0:09:38.36,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.36,0:09:40.36,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,If he's not hanging from above...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.01,0:09:45.53,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Inspector Nakamori, there's nothing \Nsticking out of this building either!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.92,0:09:50.70,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Like I figured, they would suspect that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.32,0:09:55.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But my magic isn't simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.91,0:09:59.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.96,0:10:02.78,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Well, on the eve of the main event,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.78,0:10:08.12,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,feast your eyes on the \Nmiracle I have wrought.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.53,0:10:16.56,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Senior Adviser, shouldn't \Nwe activate that trap now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.56,0:10:18.52,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.94,0:10:30.41,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Jii-chan's intel was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.83,0:10:32.87,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Well, that's enough for tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.83,0:10:39.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Well, that's enough of a preview.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.49,0:10:43.54,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Let's meet back here again \Ntomorrow night at 8:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.91,0:10:50.61,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,H-He disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.61,0:10:51.97,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,In mid-air!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.19,0:11:06.07,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Jii-chan, it's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.07,0:11:08.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The crowd's three times \Nas large tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.49,0:11:10.28,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.18,0:11:25.34,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Excuse me! You're the owner of Blue Wonder \Nand senior adviser of the Suzuki conglomerate,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.34,0:11:27.06,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Jirokichi Suzuki-san, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.06,0:11:28.08,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.08,0:11:29.97,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's almost that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.97,0:11:32.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Are your Kid countermeasures foolproof?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.12,0:11:36.10,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Last night he put on a cut-rate magic show,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.73,0:11:39.35,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,but I've got something \Nto show everyone tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.27,0:11:45.97,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'll get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.97,0:11:47.19,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.52,0:12:02.98,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Five! Four!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.98,0:12:05.21,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Three! Two!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.21,0:12:06.38,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,One!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.80,0:12:14.99,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,H-How?! Where did he come from?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.30,0:12:27.29,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Hey! What happened, number 7 chopper? Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.29,0:12:28.32,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What the...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.32,0:12:31.03,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The feed from chopper \Nnumber 7 suddenly cut out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.03,0:12:34.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This is helicopter number 7. I'm not \Nexperiencing any difficulties here...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.49,0:12:39.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Maybe the rain temporarily \Nscrambled the feed?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.49,0:12:43.30,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,No. My wager is that Kid \Nhad an assistant cut the power
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.30,0:12:45.46,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,as part of his plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.46,0:12:47.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid has assistants?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.67,0:12:49.24,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.24,0:12:52.58,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,An old man, a young woman... \NThere are various reports.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.58,0:12:54.84,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But he definitely has at least one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.47,0:12:59.88,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Get Blue Wonder inside the building!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.88,0:13:01.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This is a contest of wits!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.04,0:13:03.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.80,0:13:10.30,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's in the building!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.30,0:13:12.61,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,All right! And now I'll take the initiative.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.61,0:13:15.65,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Extinguish all the lights \Nin the building immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.38,0:13:17.48,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Turn them off?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.48,0:13:21.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's possible he's intercepting the \Nvideo footage inside the building, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.66,0:13:25.87,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,B-But why put the jewel in the museum?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.29,0:13:29.74,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The main thing is to not let him steal it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.80,0:13:37.52,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.52,0:13:39.45,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What's going on over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.45,0:13:43.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,No problems, Inspector Nakamori. We're \Ndefinitely outthinking Kid with this plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.81,0:13:45.05,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Shhh!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.87,0:13:49.95,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He may be listening in, \Nso let's cut the chatter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.95,0:13:52.60,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.60,0:13:53.98,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Everything is going smoothly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.81,0:13:59.91,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Another dud...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.91,0:14:04.19,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Ah, well, at least I got back\N at old man Jirokichi
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.19,0:14:07.25,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,by showing everyone a miracle,\N so not a bad night.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.24,0:14:18.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What's so funny...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.08,0:14:22.72,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...Kid the Phantom Thief?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.72,0:14:25.26,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,W-What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.26,0:14:29.59,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'm laughing because I kept Kid \Nfrom stealing the jewel, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.59,0:14:30.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Dumbass.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.69,0:14:35.15,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I saw right through you the moment you \Narrived at the museum on this bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.15,0:14:39.60,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then, like now, you're \Nnot wearing your goggles.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.60,0:14:44.37,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I hear it's really painful for people who \Nwear contacts not to wear goggles when riding.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.37,0:14:46.87,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This kid doesn't miss a trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.31,0:14:51.74,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And an old man riding around in a \Nshowy bike without bodyguards...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.74,0:14:55.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you had any number of chances \Nto put him to sleep and take his place.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.42,0:14:59.57,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I "silenced" the old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.57,0:15:03.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Since he's the type who wants to stand out \Nso much that he interferes with the magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.29,0:15:07.44,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I can't be Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.44,0:15:12.62,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,For example, when Kid appeared \Nearlier, I was right next to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.62,0:15:16.15,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That was the moment he performed \Nthat airwalking miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.15,0:15:19.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That was no miracle!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.20,0:15:22.86,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It was a simple trick that only \Nrequired an assistant and preparation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.86,0:15:25.90,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It must not have been that hard\N for your assistant
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.90,0:15:30.12,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,to temporarily slip into the crowd\N of hired helicopter pilots.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.12,0:15:34.33,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Jii-chan has all kinds of licenses, \Nso it was a cinch for him to be hired.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.96,0:15:40.65,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,First, you and your assistant flew \Nthe chopper over those two buildings,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.65,0:15:44.76,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,then attached a wire to one of the roofs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.36,0:15:50.48,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Toss away the camouflaging \Nblack cape into the stage smoke,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.48,0:15:52.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and Kid the Phantom Thief appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.15,0:15:59.32,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Next, your assistant in the helicopter \Nhovered directly overhead,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.32,0:16:02.93,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,so Kid was "wired" from above and the side,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.93,0:16:05.30,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,seemingly floating in mid-air.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.78,0:16:08.45,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then you just had to pretend to walk
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.45,0:16:10.91,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,to match the chopper's slow advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.91,0:16:16.84,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A music player you had in your pocket \Nplayed the sound of footsteps,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.84,0:16:21.84,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and your exceptional body performance \Nensured no one would notice you were hanging.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.84,0:16:23.30,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.59,0:16:28.73,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...for the finishing touch, your assistant \Npulled you up into the chopper,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.73,0:16:31.63,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,making it look like you \Nvanished into thin air.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.37,0:16:34.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.36,0:16:41.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Although {\i1}tonight's{\i0} Kid was just a marionette \Nto draw the police's attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.01,0:16:43.93,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It was obvious to me that \Nit was just hanging there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.93,0:16:47.08,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But you climbed that building, son.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.08,0:16:52.33,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,If there was anything hanging from a helicopter,\N you would've seen it, even a thin wire.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.33,0:16:54.53,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Preconceptions and wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.53,0:16:56.21,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Pathetic on my part.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.78,0:17:02.28,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,When the helicopter was over you,\N I didn't think you were hanging from it,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.28,0:17:04.86,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I was startled there were \Nno wires on the roof,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.86,0:17:07.76,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and the wind from the chopper \Nalso made it difficult to see,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.76,0:17:10.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and so I didn't spot your wires.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.68,0:17:15.86,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But your hooks left scratches on the roofs \Nof both buildings where they were attached.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.24,0:17:18.78,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Preconceptions...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.78,0:17:20.73,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,In magic, we call that the "reappearance."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.49,0:17:26.43,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,If you show that there's nothing there once, \Nit's hard for people to get suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.43,0:17:32.24,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,After they've checked something once,\N they don't feel the need to check again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.87,0:17:38.08,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But I'm sure you watched the footage \Nof Kid last night over and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.08,0:17:43.90,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The footage shows a bird's-eye \Nview of Kid, wires and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.90,0:17:47.05,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,but it was shot by your confederate \Nin helicopter number 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.05,0:17:52.24,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,If you'd used faked footage based \Non the museum's special exhibition,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.24,0:17:54.31,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,there's no way the wires would be showing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.77,0:17:59.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But when it started to rain, your assistant \Nnixed the idea of sending out the fake footage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.05,0:18:05.15,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Because it didn't show people at the \Nexhibition opening their umbrellas, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.50,0:18:11.82,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I bet last night's demonstration, where you \Nseemed to appear from the air, was to loosen
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.82,0:18:16.87,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,ground security so you could come in \Ndisguised as Jirokichi Suzuki without a challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.98,0:18:19.33,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But you were careless.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.33,0:18:24.90,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You were shown on TV on the bike \Nbut without the goggles on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.90,0:18:28.72,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Actually, I didn't {\i1}forget {\i0}\Nto put the goggles on...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.72,0:18:30.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I couldn't put them on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.68,0:18:33.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Because that would ruin \Nmy disguise! You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.10,0:18:38.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You sure about this? Your \Nassistant in chopper number 7...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.49,0:18:41.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He may be surrounded by police \Nhelicopters right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.94,0:18:46.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,No worries there. I'm sure \Nthe cops are in panic mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.68,0:18:50.53,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And confused by all the stickers \Nwe put on number 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.53,0:18:51.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,All the stickers?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.66,0:18:53.56,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.56,0:18:59.83,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You lightly glued on stickers over the \Noriginal number so they'd peel off in the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.83,0:19:01.22,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.22,0:19:05.17,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That way, he could slip in with the \Nother pilots without them noticing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.66,0:19:10.45,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And nobody could chase after his chopper, \Nbecause "number 7" was gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.45,0:19:13.85,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,My friend took advantage \Nof the chaos and escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.85,0:19:18.41,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,There's your Blue Wonder! \NA miraculous aerial escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.41,0:19:19.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Aerial?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.96,0:19:23.02,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The "blue" in  Blue Wonder refers to the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.02,0:19:24.80,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Same difference, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.80,0:19:27.73,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The blue of the sky is reflected \Nin the blue of the sea, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.73,0:19:30.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's like detective and phantom thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.67,0:19:32.92,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,They appear to be as different \Nas heaven and earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.92,0:19:36.36,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,but look closely, and you'll see \Nthey're both insolent fellows who use
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.36,0:19:40.71,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,the key of curiosity to pry open something \Nthat someone else wants to keep shut.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.71,0:19:44.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Dumbass. The blue of the sky and sea
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.67,0:19:46.80,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,are from the color's \Ndiffusion and reflection.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.80,0:19:49.76,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's because they're completely \Ndifferent substances.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.76,0:19:51.17,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,They're not the same thing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.66,0:19:54.88,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You can see the proof in a puddle,\N which isn't blue, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.88,0:19:57.31,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You have no dreams, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.31,0:20:00.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,If I talked about dreams all the time, \NI wouldn't be able to see through to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.94,0:20:05.00,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That aside, do you really think you'll \Ncapture me with that tranquilizer gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.00,0:20:08.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,If I get knocked out at this speed, \Nwe'll get into a major wreck.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.40,0:20:09.70,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.70,0:20:12.27,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I won't shoot you until the bike stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.27,0:20:16.62,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I've already contacted Inspector Nakamori, \Nso he'll be the one to arrest you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.34,0:20:18.89,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Like I'm gonna stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.89,0:20:22.33,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This is something old man \NJirokichi is proud about, I bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.33,0:20:26.29,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The bike has a trick you can do \Nto get rid of excess weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.19,0:20:35.92,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,See you around, great detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.92,0:20:39.16,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,In the end, I wasn't really after the jewel.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.16,0:20:42.60,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This time was just about \Ntaking up the gauntlet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.60,0:20:44.45,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.23,0:20:49.77,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I won't shoot you until the bike stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.58,0:20:53.15,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That little turd hit the gas tank!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.05,0:21:12.08,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,For them, don't be bound by theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.08,0:21:16.02,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,but intoxicate them with a display \Nof brilliant magic that verges
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.02,0:21:17.80,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,on the impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.80,0:21:24.09,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,If you can do that, your troublesome \Nheckler will turn into an ardent fan.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.68,0:21:29.08,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This is how a true magician ought to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.96,0:21:35.03,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What kind of magic should I use \Nto boggle his mind next time?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.38,0:21:42.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Tonight's performance was \Na miraculous mid-air walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.67,0:21:47.38,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'm sure even the pint-sized \Ndetective was impressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.38,0:21:51.61,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Well, see you next illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.35,0:23:22.91,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Sheesh! That brat's gonna get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.91,0:23:25.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I was almost burnt toast back there!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.20,0:23:27.37,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But my next prey is...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.37,0:23:31.31,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He's after the world's biggest emerald, \Nwhich is being used as a prop in a play!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.31,0:23:33.09,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Who gave you permission to do the preview?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.09,0:23:33.98,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What's the difference?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.98,0:23:35.23,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It makes a difference!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.23,0:23:38.73,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Next time on {\i1}Magic Kaito 1412{\i0}: \NGreen Dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.23,0:23:38.73,Signs,,0,0,0,,Green Dream
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.73,0:23:41.61,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Step right this way! Watch carefully!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.61,0:23:43.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You're the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.20,0:23:45.16,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right! It's me! Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.16,0:23:46.25,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Ahem...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.25,0:23:48.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Don't miss the illusion!
